EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Hearing Held by Committee
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the removal of graffiti from commercial and residential buildings, and in relation to establishing a process whereby the city may clean graffiti from these buildings.
EventItemMatterName: Imposing a fine against the owners of commercial buildings and residential buildings of six or more units who do not remove graffiti from their premises.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Hearing Held by Committee
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the police department to submit to the council reports of crime in parks and playgrounds.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring NYPD to submit to the Council reports of crime in areas under the jurisdiction of the Department of Parks and Recreation.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Hearing Held by Committee
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the possession and sale of graffiti instruments.
EventItemMatterName: Possession and sale of graffiti instruments.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Hearing Held by Committee
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to community service for certain graffiti offenses.
EventItemMatterName: Mandating community service for certain graffiti offenses.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Hearing Held by Committee
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to adopt legislation that provides for the civil commitment of sexually violent predators to protect the public from those whose mental abnormalities makes them likely to commit sexually violent crimes.
EventItemMatterName: Provides for civil commitment of sexually violent predators to protect the public from those whose mental abnormalities makes them likely to commit sexually violent crimes.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Hearing Held by Committee
EventItemTitle: Resolution supporting legislation increasing the number of sex offenders required to register for life.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring all sex offenders to register for life.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Hearing Held by Committee
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to increase penalties for those who commit sex offenses against children, similar to provisions adopted in Florida as part of the Jessica Lunsford Act.
EventItemMatterName: Enact sex offense provisions similar to those adopted in Florida, as part of the Jessica Lunsford Act.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Hearing Held by Committee
EventItemTitle: Resolution in support of legislation that improves the national program to register and monitor individuals who commit sex offenses against children.
EventItemMatterName: Support of U.S. Senate bill S.1086, which improves the national program to register and monitor individuals who commit sex offenses.
